Jordan Invites Companies to Bid for Water Project, Times Says

-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 
2011-04-07T09:19:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/jordan-invites-companies-to-bid-for-water-project-times-says.html
Mitsubishi Corp. (8058)  and  China ’s
Sinohydro Corp. are among companies invited to bid for work on
the  Red Sea Project  for desalinating water, the Jordan Times
said, citing Minister of Water and Irrigation Mohammad Najjar.  Orascom Construction Industries, Egypt’s largest publicly
traded builder, was also selected to bid by September for the
contract, as were  Samsung C&T Corp. (000830)  of  South Korea , Saudi
Arabia’s ACWA Power and  Acciona SA (ANA)  of Spain, the newspaper
reported. The project aims to ease Jordan’s water shortage by
desalinating water from the  Red Sea .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Amman at 
 nrazzouk2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  